## Implementation Plan (6 Phases)

### Phase 1 — Monorepo Scaffold
- Init pnpm workspace root with `pnpm-workspace.yaml`
- Create `apps/server`, `apps/client`, `packages/shared` directories
- Configure TypeScript (strict mode, path aliases, project references across packages)
- Set up ESLint + Prettier (shared config)
- Set up Vite for client bundle
- Configure concurrent dev runner at root (`pnpm dev` runs all packages)

### Phase 2 — Shared Package (`packages/shared`)
- TypeScript types: `Player`, `Room`, `Bomb`, `Item`, `GameState`, `Tile`, all socket event payload interfaces
- Game constants: grid dimensions (15×13), tick rate (20 TPS), bomb fuse (3s), default blast radius (1), item drop rates
- Pure utility functions: grid position helpers, explosion spread calculator, collision detection

### Phase 3 — Server Core (`apps/server`)
- Express app with CORS, cookie-parser, helmet
- MongoDB connection + Mongoose models (players, rooms, game_sessions)
- Room manager — in-memory Map, create/join/leave/destroy lifecycle
- Socket.io integration: connect, disconnect, room events, input events
- Game engine: fixed tick loop, input queue processing, bomb placement + timer, explosion propagation (4 directions, chain detonation), item drop on soft wall destroy, player death detection
- Player identity via UUID cookie (`player_id`)
- Latency ping/pong handler

### Phase 4 — Client Core (`apps/client`)
- `index.html` + Canvas element setup
- Socket.io client connection with auto-reconnect
- Lobby UI: create room form, join by room ID form, room ID display/copy
- Waiting room UI: player list with colors, "Start Game" button for creator
- Canvas renderer:
  - Grid (tile colors per type)
  - Players (unique color per lobby slot, name label above)
  - Bombs (fuse animation)
  - Explosions (flash effect)
  - Items on floor
  - HUD (bomb count, blast radius, latency badge)
- Input handler: WASD / arrow keys for movement, Space for bomb drop
- Latency measurement: ping every 2s, display RTT color-coded (green <80ms, yellow <200ms, red ≥200ms)

### Phase 5 — Game Loop Integration
- Full flow: lobby → 3s countdown → in-game → game over screen → back to lobby
- Client-side movement interpolation for smooth rendering between server ticks
- Bomb countdown visual (shrinking indicator)
- Death animation + player removal
- Winner announcement overlay

### Phase 6 — Polish & Deployment
- Responsive canvas scaling (window resize handler)
- `docker/docker-compose.yml` for local dev stack (server + client + mongodb)
- `apps/server/Dockerfile` — Node.js multi-stage build
- `apps/client/Dockerfile` — Vite build → Nginx static serve
- `docker/nginx/nginx.conf` — reverse proxy, TLS termination, WebSocket upgrade headers
- Google Cloud deployment (asia-south1): container registry push, Cloud Run or GCE config
- Environment variable documentation

