## Socket Event Reference

### Client → Server
| Event | Payload | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `room:create` | `{ displayName }` | Create a new room, receive roomId back |
| `room:join` | `{ roomId, displayName }` | Join existing room by ID |
| `room:start` | — | Creator starts the game (min 2 players, or solo for dev) |
| `player:input` | `{ dir: 'up'|'down'|'left'|'right'|null, action: 'bomb'|null }` | Movement + bomb drop |
| `room:leave` | — | Graceful disconnect from room |
| `latency:ping` | `{ clientTime: number }` | Sent every 2s for RTT measurement |

### Server → Client
| Event | Payload | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `room:state` | `RoomState` | Full room state snapshot on join |
| `room:update` | `Partial<RoomState>` | Lobby changes (player joined/left, status) |
| `game:tick` | `GameStateDiff` | Incremental game state diff at 20 TPS |
| `game:countdown` | `{ seconds: number }` | Pre-game countdown |
| `game:over` | `{ winnerId: string \| null }` | Game ended (null = draw) |
| `latency:pong` | `{ clientTime: number }` | Echo for RTT calculation |
| `error` | `{ code: string, message: string }` | Error feedback to client |

